• Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. BRANDFORT - Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) leader Julius Malema is expected to address a memorial service in honour of struggle stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. The memorial service will be held at the Majwemasweu stadium in Deeplevel in Brandfort on Wednesday morning. The town is where Madikizela-Mandela was put under house arrest for eight years by the then-apartheid government. The EFF will host a memorial in honour of Madikizela-Mandela under the following details: Malema, who had close relations with Madikizela-Mandela, had earlier told a group gathered outside her Soweto home, that South Africa failed Madikizela-Mandela. READ: Details of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela's funeral finalised He said Madikizela-Mandela should have become South Africa's president, instead of Jacob Zuma. “Had they allowed Winnie Mandela to stand as deputy president, we would not have known a president called Zuma,” he said. Madikizela-Mandela passed on at Johannesburg’s Milpark Hospital after a long illness on 1 April. She will be laid to rest on 14 April. eNCA